<div class="course-mainbar lecture-content">
  <h2 id="lecture_heading" class="section-title" data-lecture-id="1117411" data-next-lecture-id="1117631" data-lecture-url="/courses/digital-marketing-with-interactive-calculators/lectures/1117411" data-next-lecture-url="/courses/digital-marketing-with-interactive-calculators/lectures/1117631" ,="" data-previous-lecture-url="/courses/digital-marketing-with-interactive-calculators/lectures/1117403" data-previous-lecture-id="1117403">
    <i class="fa fa-file-text"></i>
    &nbsp;
    What kind of a calculator should be build?
</h2>

  <!-- Attachment Blocks -->

  <div class="lecture-attachment">
    <div class="attachment-data"></div>
    
      <div class="attachment-data"></div>
<div class="lecture-text-container">
<p></p><p><title></title>
</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong><em>Sky's the limit here.</em></strong></span>
</p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial;">The right kind of calculator depends on your imagination, your product needs and the messaging direction your team wants to take.</span>
</p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial;">But whatever you do, do not stray away from the metrics that are important to your customers. What do they really need? Are they driven by prices, discounts, or RoI? Do they need help with a big, intimidating, potentially stressful decision? Does their choice involve data? A calculator can be the perfect tool designed to answer those questions. Here are few types of calculators that have been successful:<br><br><br><img alt="Mobile App Cost Calculator.png" height="323" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/C6suwhluWKBbF07QoT8SvDiiy2zdaGptwkgKdlklGBepHGQ__b0H52TxsufAbxb4wrHdShyGMh76nnkKndAzA5JvCrriJr6TSatqaz3VNxEc807O7oAJfh-aAaf0_tCi1GTmZnaC" width="356" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; width: 356px; height: 323px; display: block; margin: auto;"></span>
</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;">
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><em><span style="font-size: 14px;">VenturePact’s “How much to build an app?” Calculator</span><br><br></em>
  </span>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Simple Cost Calculators:</strong> These are the best props to spring up while you're rambling away at an interested client about your product. A quick tap here and a few inputs there- and voila! you have an estimate. The key here is to address the needs of the customer, not of your own business. So instead of pricing your own product, help address the customer's concern. So if you’re building apps, rather than saying “Get a quote from [company name]”, say “How much you should be paying for app development?”.<br><br></span></li>
</ul>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;">
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><img alt="apprenda_roi_calculator.jpg" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/WgU-Ki-IMwLeX4oAkuB5aQCNh-SRAD2ot8ve_l-Rs82aTvo9DzYY9dpMIkDvYXXEBAlPgk4ErsMkoq8Dp06XFdz98ghDYCtS5Rp5EyqwDxWIunMw8QoGzrAI0IbjZPkftIkq77oQ" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; width: 333px; height: 200px;">
  </span>
</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;">
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size:11px;"><em><span style="font-size: 14px;">Apprenda makes a clear value proposition with an ROI calculator.</span><br><br></em></span>
  </span>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>RoI Calculator:</strong> The quintessential question your marketing and sales needs to answer is what is the return on investment on your product, what is the value proposition in hard numbers. Every customer has this question and the answer depends on various factors and attributes which make RoI estimators some of the best converting calculators.<br><br><br><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/41n0Bo7MERGVYwh0Gf4fDrsVVMBQsft7UpnN2o6VswsO33Wcxs4B2jCq48FhtUwGa00mhPZR63KUyGJBupLXBgyfs-tOD50uzl0WlFjr_3KOzbnbW0Gbvbw9JsuD2s6ZVcAvyD0w" class="img-responsive" alt="" width="383" height="234" style="display: block; margin: auto; width: 383px; height: 234px;"></span></li>
</ul>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size:11px;"><em><span style="font-size: 14px;">Harvard Financial Aid Calculator<br><br></span></em></span>
  </span>
</p>
<div>
</div>
<ul>
  <li>
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Savings/Financial Aid Calculators:</strong> A few years ago, universities across the world found out that Financial Aid tools were an average college applicant’s best friend. That's why every other university in the world now has its own <em>net price calculators</em>. These are simple tools to help prospective students and their guardians figure out what a higher education might actually cost them.<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/LF4V9TktyoqB7r5g1psB-zaQ2ueziFa8ykwUaaSbPjsPGZ9v0W9OfSeucY1Dbw33z9sbVhjV_AI3sBta_X7E_4S_B8NDYYc7FacyScVsb18iBJ7wnCMzMPfKcI_NwA4PAZx-1L0l" class="img-responsive" width="347" height="343" alt="" style="width: 347px; height: 343px; display: block; margin: auto;"></span></li>
</ul>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;"><em>Bigfuture Co's University Cost Calculator</em>
</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><em><br></em>
  </span>
</p>
<div>
</div>
<ul>
  <li>
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Comparative Calculators:</strong> Businesses have used this type of calculator in many ways. Usually, third party aggregators use it to help visitors decide for themselves what product suits their needs the best. For example, the US College Board helps students make an informed decision by letting them compare total spendings for each school with a calculator.<br><br></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
  <li>
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Real Time Calculators:</strong> These are calculators that show the results while the questions are being answered as opposed to showing results after all the questions are answered. Such calculators let the users play with various inputs and see how those inputs affect the final result in real time. Say you were building a cancer risk calculator. You might want to let the users see how their body weight might affect their risk of getting cancer. So they can play with the calculator and see what weight they need to be in order to minimize the risk of cancer.<br><br></span></li>
</ul>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;">
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/YmkBUtd19jNTKm0lJLXG7WIwYX91ayuoNir96pNHtHI-Whd6lyyP2v_HyAYFxoeUt_ckzmGmjMO4S1GgSyG5ZVyXWK5cO0uYv-nZ88Xih5ICmSNBO43d-OjOrZOvsixD7dB3LXLe" width="481" height="308" alt="" style="color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: 308px; width: 481px; display: block; margin: auto;">
  </span>
</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22.4px; border: none; box-shadow: none; color: rgb(61, 85, 87); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif; text-align: center; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;">
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><em>Hubspot's Pro Plan Calculator<br><br></em>
  </span>
</p>
<div>
</div>
<ul>
  <li>
  <span style="font-family: Arial;"><strong>Complex Calculators:</strong> If your prospects are struggling with making buying decisions owing to a complex thought process, then you’ve found your goal. Designing a calculator that provides your buyers with as much information as possible to help them easily consider all their options will be your best bet. Here’s an example of HubSpot's pricing calculator clearly breaking down their price schedules.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial;">This way you lay all the cards on the table, letting your buyers think they’re in control of the situation. Knowing what they're in for from a pricing perspective before they spend any time on the phone with you is a great ‘trust move’.<br><br></span>
</p><p></p>
</div>

    
